text.id: One of the downstream roles of color contrast detectors is to make line detectors respond to changes in color across the line. In this circuit, we will see how this is done.

g.id: A (slightly tilted) horizontal line detector is excited by horizontal color contrasts of all hues, and inhibited by vertical ones.
A vertical line detector is excited by vertical color contrasts of all hues, and inhibited by horizontal ones.
